Executive Profile
B. Bernard   Burns Jr.Co-Founder and Managing Director, Red Iron Partners, LLCAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 2 Board Members in 2 different organizations across 3 different industries.See Board Relationships68--
Background

		Mr. B. Bernard Burns, Jr. is Co-Founder of Red Iron Partners, LLC and serves as its Managing Director. Mr. Burns is a Co-Founder of McGuireWoods Capital Group and has been its Managing Director since 2001. He is of counsel to the law firm of McGuireWoods LLP and served as its Partner from 2001 to 2011. He served in various executive capacities with United Dominion Industries Limited, a diversified industrial manufacturer, from 1989 to 2001, including as Senior Vice President ... and General Counsel from 1993 to 1996, Executive Vice President and Chief Administrative Officer in 2000 and as president of various operating segments and divisions from 1996 to 1999 and from 2000 to 2001. At United Dominion, he played an integral part in transforming United Dominion from an engineering and construction entity to an international provider of diversified manufacturing products. These activities included direct responsibility for numerous mergers and acquisitions, asset dispositions and recoveries (including a $36 million Canadian pension plan surplus recapture and litigation settlement), significant personnel recruitment and development and implementation of a sophisticated corporate governance program. As a member of United Dominion's Senior Management team, he was directly responsible for legal, human resources, planning and development, corporate communications and transportation functions. He worked directly with United Dominion’s Board of Directors and its compensation and human resources and corporate governance committees. He created and managed United Dominion's successful OPEX Team, consisting of young managers in various positions within United Dominion who performed operational improvement activities in a number of operating units. While President of three separate business segments, he was responsible for the strategic direction and financial results of over 20 separate operating divisions. In this role, he led efforts resulting in the consummation of over 20 acquisitions and divestitures in these business units. He also led these segments in developing and implementing extensive cost reduction and margin improvement programs. He was President of Door Products Division. Prior to joining United Dominion in 1989, he practiced corporate law for 16 years with a large Charlotte, North Carolina, law firm. He has been an Independent Director of EnPro Industries, Inc. since December 31, 2011. He serves as  a Member of the boards of Directors of Robert Family Holdings, Inc. (also known as Siegel-Robert, Inc.) and Spartan Light Metal Products, Inc., both headquartered in St. Louis, Missouri and of Crowder Construction Company, headquartered in Charlotte, North Carolina. He has also served on the boards of a number of non-profit business, educational and charitable organizations, including the Ben Craig Center business incubator, the N.C. Governor’s Commission on Business and Industry and the Metrolina Entrepreneurial Council. Mr. Burns received his J.D. from Duke Law School, where he was a member of the Order of the Coif and of the Editorial Board of the Duke Law Journal and received his B.A. from Furman University (Summa Cum Laude). He also was a 1992 participant in the Fuqua School’s Executive Management Program.Read Full Background




